"Take the easy road and at the end, you will feel you have achieved nothing. Try the difficult shit and you’ll enjoy your successes.\n\n- Michael R. Fletcher, Ghosts of Tomorrow\n|\nWhat is important is not what you hear said, it's what you observe.\n\n- Michael Connelly, Trunk Music\n|\nAsk me no questions, and I'll tell you no fibs.\n\n- Oliver Goldsmith, She Stoops to Conquer\n|\nPeople who give the best are those who give of themselves – your time, talents, words, knowledge.\n\n- Omoakhuana\n|\nTrust me, Bea, you are on your way. It’s about acknowledging where you are and knowing that you are okay. The universe has your back and so do I.\n\n- Sadeqa Johnson, And Then There Was Me\n|\nLike freshly cut roses, I place life in a vase... of love.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nThere is nothing to writing, all you have to do is, sit on the computer and bleed your thoughts.\n\n- Santosh\n|\nEducation is the fertilizer for the mind, the seeds for success, and the eye opener for life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf you had to identify, in one word, the reason why the human race has not achieved, and never will achieve, its full potential, that word would be 'meetings.\n\n- Dave\n|\nPlace yourself... You are either a.) part of the problem; b.) part of the solution, or c.) part of the landscape.\n\n- James D. Sass, Essays in Satanism\n|\nI take thee at thy word:Call me but love, and I'll be new baptized;Henceforth I never will be Romeo.\n\n- William Shakespeare, Romeo and Juliet\n|\nCome out, O lions, and shake off the ancient mysticism and prejudices.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Islamophobic Civilization: Voyage of Acceptance\n|\nHappiness is a spiritual dimension; therefore its source should also be spiritual, not material.\n\n- Sunday\n|\ni was lieing to myself when I thought I was lost, I have never been lost - I just wasn't ready to be found.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nThe search for truth takes you where the evidence leads you, even if, at first, you don't want to go there.\n\n- Bart D. Ehrman, Forged: Writing in the Name of God\n|\nWithin us is Energy which when channelized, spirals into Inspiration.\n\n- RVM\n|\nNo matter how qualified or deserving we are, we will never reach a better life until we can imagine it for ourselves and allow ourselves to have it.\n\n- Richard\n|\nYou endure what is unbearable, and you bear it. That is all.\n\n- Cassandra Clare, Clockwork Princess\n|\nContrary to what we've been told, life is simple. We complicate matters with our choices.\n\n- Michelle\n|\nTo become a better you, look nowhere else for another alarm to blow before you wake up. Get up and rise up.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nIn success, knowledge - In failure, lessons.\n\n- Garry\n|\nI looked to the ceiling and told God, “God, next time I want an adventure, strike me with lightning. You have my permission.\n\n- Kristen Ashley, The Gamble\n|\nNever give up hope, no matter how dark things may seem.\n\n- A.\n|\nArranged Conversation and Pre-Planned Emotions never Works in real life, and Always Comes with Bad Ending .\n\n- Yaganesh\n|\nThe world the Citadel is building has no place in it for sorcery or prophecy or glass candles, much less for dragons.\n\n- George R.R. Martin, A Feast for Crows\n|\nWhen privacy is criminalized, only criminals will have privacy.\n\n- Daniel Suarez, Change Agent\n|\nMy friends, love is better than anger. Hope is better than fear. Optimism is better than despair. So let us be loving, hopeful and optimistic. And we'll change the world.\n\n- Jack\n|\nIn a story you had to find a reason, but real life gets on very well without even Freudian motivations.\n\n- Anthony Burgess, Earthly Powers\n|\nRock and roll, big band, the blues. He loved them all. He would close his eyes and with a blissful smile begin to move to his own sense of rhythm. It wasn't always pretty.\n\n- Mitch Albom, Tuesdays with Morrie\n|\nyou give your best for today, you create a greater tomorrow.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nDon't be afraid to be successful,and keep in your mind that you don't have another choice be successful or be successful\n\n- Aymen\n|\nI celebrate myself, and sing myself, And what I assume you shall assume,For every atom belonging to me as good belongs to you.\n\n- Walt Whitman, Leaves of Grass\n|\nYou can’t conceive, my child, nor can I or anyone the … appalling … strangeness of the mercy of God.\n\n- Graham Greene, Brighton Rock\n|\nGod has judged me all my life. But that is God's privilege, my lady. Not yours.\n\n- Barbara Hambly, The Armies of Daylight\n|\nI've forgotten most of what I've read and, frankly, it never seemed very important to me or to the world.\n\n- Leonard Cohen, Beautiful Losers\n|\nDon’t waste your time in anger, regrets, worries, and grudges. Life is too short to be unhappy.\n\n- Roy\n|\nImagine if you were performing at your full potential, the lives you would change - including yours. Just imagine...\n\n- Bobby\n|\nEnd? No, the journey doesn't end here. Death is just another path. One that we all must take.\n\n- J.R.R. Tolkien, The Return of the King\n|\nBut now that I’m scrubbingtoilets on my hands & knees,with four degrees,I realize that one escape routeleads to another\n\n- Phil Volatile, Crushed Black Velvet\n|\nI was a new person then, I knew things I had not known before, I knew things that you can know only if you have been through what I had just been through.\n\n- Jamaica Kincaid, The Autobiography of My Mother\n|\nWhere should I go?' -Alice. 'That depends on where you want to end up.' - The Cheshire Cat.\n\n- Lewis Carroll, Alice's Adventures in Wonderland & Through the Looking-Glass\n|\nWhy, then, should we ever sink overwhelmed with distress, when life is so soon over, and death is so certain an entrance to happiness – to glory?\n\n- Charlotte Brontë, Jane Eyre\n|\nWhat the new mate, sports car, or unexpected check could never do, Christ says, 'I Can.' You'll love how he achieves it. He reconnects your soul with God.\n\n- Max\n|\nThere is a thin line that separates laughter and pain, comedy and tragedy, humor and hurt.\n\n- Erma\n|\nFor some people, “the point of no return” begins at the very moment their souls become aware of each others’ existence.\n\n- C.\n|\nLet’s face it, life is trivial, and my guess is that dying imparts very little wisdom on those in process.\n\n- Sue Grafton, I is for Innocent\n|\nPrate not to me of suicide, Faint heart in battle, not for pride I say Endure, but that such end denied Makes welcomer yet the death that's to be died.\n\n- Stevie Smith, Selected Poems\n|\nBe creative, be useful, be practical, be generous and finish big\n\n- Lisa Genova, Still Alice\n|\nEveryone is their own, though they are so alone. They all sit on their imagined thrones, made only of their own bones. Ego and pride make exquisite delusional cushions.\n\n- Hubert\n|\nI felt as if I were riding a pendulum. Just as I would swing into the abyss of hopelessness, the pendulum would swing back with some small goodness.\n\n- Ruta Sepetys, Between Shades of Gray\n|\nlife is either a reproducible, almost commonplace manifestation of matter, given certain conditions, or a miracle. Too many steps are involved to allow for something in between.\n\n- Christian\n|\nYou are here because some sliver of existence within you says that you are a born fighter. That you will put your life before others, and stand when others fall.\n\n- Melissa\n|\nMarriage is not a process for prolonging the life of love, sir. It merely mummifies its corpse.\n\n- P.G. Wodehouse, The Small Bachelor\n|\nI wonder what Piglet is doing,' thought Pooh. 'I wish I were there to be doing it, too.\n\n- A.A. Milne, Winnie-the-Pooh\n|\nThe Clayr saw me, the Wallmaker made me, the King quenched me, the Abhorsen wields me so that no Dead shall walk in Life. For this is not their path.\n\n- Garth Nix, Sabriel\n|\nBlood, sweat and respect. The first two you give, the last one you get.\n\n- Unknown\n|\n‎Life is a shipwreck, but we must not forget to sing in the lifeboats.\n\n- Voltaire\n|\nWriting is the delicate, difficult, and dangerous means of succeeding in avowing the unavowable.\n\n- Hélène\n|\nWe are all of us born with a letter inside us, and that only if we are true to ourselves, may we be allowed to read it before we die.\n\n- Douglas\n|\nVulnerability creates unimaginable space to build each other up, as much as it creates ample room to tear each other down.\n\n- Craig\n|\nYour universe is not out there. You create it every moment and every day with your thoughts, ideas, perceptions, and imaginations.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf you can have everything at fifty that you wanted when you were fifteen, you're happy.\n\n- Alfred Bester, The Stars My Destination\n|\nAccept criticism. If you do not offer your work for criticism and accept that criticism, meaning give it serious thought and attention, then you will never improve.\n\n- Theodora\n|\nThere are fears that are worth facing and there are fears that are not. You don't have to face all fears, only the ones that are relevant to you at that moment in time.\n\n- Kim Ha Campbell, Inner Peace Outer Abundance\n|\nRather than wasting time on yesterday that is gone, it is better to invest your time in Tomorrow that is not yet born.\n\n- RVM\n|\nI was very afraid at the beginning, until Master told me that pain isn't the truth; it's what you have to get through in order to find the truth.\n\n- Deepak Chopra, The Return of Merlin\n|\nYou and I have a connection that nothing, not on heaven or earth, or even hell, could ever break. If you want to talk to me, talk to me. I’ll hear you…\n\n- Cynthia\n|\nIt’s my life and I’m not afraid to LIVE it! I would rather experience the ups and downs of a life I have chosen, than to suffer the regret of a life I have settled for.\n\n- Steve\n|\nWith a secret like that, at some point the secret itself becomes irrelevant. The fact that you kept it does not.\n\n- Sara Gruen, Water for Elephants\n|\nIn 1994, the average person spent $79 on books as compared to $56 on recorded music.\n\n- Richard\n|\nEducation is our passport to the future, for tomorrow belongs to the people who prepare for it today.\n\n- Malcolm\n|\nIn wine there is wisdom, in beer there is Freedom, in water there is bacteria.\n\n- Benjamin\n|\nI wonder if fears ever really go away, or if they just lose their power over us.\n\n- Veronica Roth, Allegiant\n|\nTo be loved is all I need, And whom I love, I love indeed.\n\n- Samuel Taylor Coleridge, The Complete Poems\n|\nTo deliver your own personal maximum, you’ll realise there are no shortcuts; if you want to be a champion it is all about rolling your sleeves up and getting stuck in.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all of Us: 12 Rules for Success\n|\nBut do not fall only for what can be seen,there is more than just beauty and pleasure...\n\n- Carol\n|\nTrue love will break you, it devotes to break your beat up, broken heart awaiting to repair and align you to your true purpose.\n\n- John\n|\nNo other thing or no other person is going to make me happy in life, I just have to do that myself.\n\n- Greg\n|\nWhat but a pestilential vapour can hover over society when its chief director is only instructed in the invention of crimes, or the stupid routine of childish ceremonies?\n\n- Mary Wollstonecraft, A Vindication of the Rights of Woman\n|\nYou can build a business, or you can run it, but there’s only two ways it can be run, you can run it straight, or you can run it into the ground.\n\n- John\n|\nI think of life as a good book. The further you get into it, the more it begins to make sense.\n\n- Harold\n|\nFailure is when you give up. A real winner is someone that doesn't give up, even when it feels like they are losing.\n\n- Joshua\n|\n...'By wisdom a house is built up,And by discernment it is made secure.By knowledge its rooms are filledWith all sorts of precious and pleasant treasures.'– Proverbs 24:3, 4\n\n- Jehovah, New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures\n|\nNah,' I said. 'But if it does, just tell him I said to get back on the bike.''What?''He'll understand.\n\n- Sarah\n|\nGetting through life without a lot of money, possessions, and/or friends is admirable, especially if it is by choice.\n\n- Mokokoma\n|\nI like the truth, even when it does trouble me.\n\n- Juliet Marillier, Wildwood Dancing\n|\nTo enjoy life, enjoy the moment.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThe most wonderful and the strongest things in the world, you know, are just the things which no one can see.\n\n- Charles Kingsley, The Water-Babies\n|\nWhen storms come, we naturally want to run. What might happen in your friendships if you learned instead to stay put when storms hit?\n\n- Afton Rorvik, Storm Sisters: Friends Though All Seasons\n|\nLet your action manifest your thought, your belief and your passion.\n\n- Mohammed\n|\nWhen you know that you know to the extent of committing your life to a just cause, then nothing will be able to stop you.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nWhoever knows God, depart from evil.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWe learn words by rote, but not their meaning; that must be paid for with our life-blood, and printed in the subtle fibres of our nerves.\n\n- George Eliot, The Lifted Veil\n|\nThe small wisdom is like water in a glass:clear, transparent, pure.The great wisdom is like the water in the sea:dark, mysterious, impenetrable.\n\n- Rabindranath\n|\nThere may be human joy in doing good with definite purpose, but they who do good expecting nothing in return know a joy that is divine.\n\n- Maurice Maeterlinck, Wisdom And Destiny\n|\nLuck, I believe, is where preparation meets opportunity.\n\n- Marcella Purnama, What I Wish I Had Known\n|\nWherever you are, be ready to create the enabling spiritual atmosphere for the sake of the kingdom of God.\n\n- Sunday\n|\nBecause 'You're perfect just the way you are,' is what your guidance counselor says. And she's an alcoholic.\n\n- Libba Bray, Beauty Queens\n|\nStep follows step,Hope follows Courage,Set your face towards danger,Set your heart on victory.\n\n- Gail Carson Levine, The Two Princesses of Bamarre\n|\nA novel must show how the world truly is, how characters genuinely think, how events actually occur. A novel should somehow reveal the true source of our actions.\n\n- Kevin Hood, Becoming Jane"